SAPL Node - Getting Started
===========================

This directory (/var/lib/sapl) is where the PDP looks for
.saplbundle files. The node is configured in BUNDLES mode with
signature verification enabled by default.

The node will not start until bundle security is configured.
You must either provide a signing key or explicitly allow unsigned
bundles before the service can run.


Quick Start (signed bundles)
----------------------------

All commands that read or write /var/lib/sapl/ or /etc/sapl/
require sudo. The data directory is only accessible to the sapl
service account to protect policy confidentiality.

1. Generate a signing keypair (one-time):

   sudo sapl bundle keygen -o /etc/sapl/signing

   This creates signing.pem (private key) and signing.pub (public key).
   Keep the private key secure. The public key goes into the config.

2. Build and sign a bundle from the example policies:

   sudo sapl bundle create -i /var/lib/sapl/example -o /var/lib/sapl/default.saplbundle -k /etc/sapl/signing.pem

3. Configure the public key in /etc/sapl/application.yml.
   Uncomment both the "bundle-security:" line AND the
   "public-key-path:" line beneath it:

   io.sapl.pdp.embedded:
     bundle-security:
       public-key-path: /etc/sapl/signing.pub

4. Restart the service:

   sudo systemctl restart sapl

5. Verify:

   curl -s http://localhost:8443/actuator/health | jq .

   You should see "status": "UP".

The PDP watches this directory for changes. When you deploy a new
bundle, the PDP reloads automatically without a restart.


Writing Your Own Policies
-------------------------

Replace the example with your own policies:

1. Create a directory with your .sapl files and a pdp.json.
   The pdp.json must contain a "configurationId" field that
   uniquely identifies this configuration version. Example:

   {
     "configurationId": "my-app-v1",
     "algorithm": {
       "votingMode": "PRIORITY_DENY",
       "defaultDecision": "DENY",
       "errorHandling": "PROPAGATE"
     }
   }

2. Build and sign: sapl bundle create -i ./my-policies -o /var/lib/sapl/default.saplbundle -k /etc/sapl/signing.pem
3. The PDP reloads automatically

See /var/lib/sapl/example/ for a starting point.


Disabling Signature Verification
---------------------------------

For development or evaluation, you can opt out of signature
verification. Add to /etc/sapl/application.yml:

   io.sapl.pdp.embedded:
     bundle-security:
       allowUnsigned: true

The node logs a warning on every startup when signature verification
is disabled. Do not use this setting in production.


